s` for inserting. I also want to manage transaction controls carefully to speed things up!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering test class design**\\n\\nI'm working on a test class named RAFileNIOTest. I note that public methods could be beneficial, but currently, existing methods are package-private. I’m thinking about using `@Timeout(60)` to ensure that the unit test runs within a bounded time limit. This could be a helpful addition, ensuring the test completes in under 60 seconds. I'll need to remember to import the JUnit Timeout for this to work properly!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_apqT5nh0GPRGclBEOE9klq6Q|fc_0a23d5d0603067150169f91cb075a481a1ad133b81e6e4c8ab", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.hsqldb/hsqldb/2.4.1/src/test/java/org_hsqldb/hsqldb/RAFileNIOTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_hsqldb.hsqldb;\n\nimport org.hsqldb.jdbc.JDBCDriver;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Timeout;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.io.TempDir;\n\nimport java.nio.file.Path;\nimport java.sql.Connection;\nimport java.sql.PreparedStatement;\nimport java.sql.ResultSet;\nimport java.sql.SQLException;\nimport java.sql.Statement;\nimport java.util.Properties;\n\nimport static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertArrayEquals;\nimport static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertEquals;\nimport static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertTrue;\n\npublic class RAFileNIOTest {\n    private static final JDBCDriver DRIVER = new JDBCDriver();\n    private static final int PAYLOAD_SIZE = 2048;\n    private static final int ROW_COUNT = 6000;\n    private static final int BATCH_SIZE = 250;\n\n    @TempDir\n    private Path temporaryDirectory;\n\n    @Test\n    @Timeout(60)\n    void closesMappedCachedTableStorage() throws Exception {\n        Path databasePath = temporaryDirectory.resolve(\"database\").resolve(\"sample\");\n        byte[] payload = createPayload();\n\n        try (Connection connection = openFileDatabase(databasePath)) {\n            createNioCachedTable(connection);\n            insertRows(connection, payload);\n            assertCachedDataIsReadable(connection, payload);\n            shutdown(connection);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static Connection openFileDatabase(Path databasePath) throws SQLException {\n        Properties properties = new Properties();\n\n        properties.setProperty(\"user\", \"SA\");\n        properties.setProperty(\"password\", \"\");\n\n        return DRIVER.connect(\"jdbc:hsqldb:file:\" + databasePath.toAbsolutePath(), properties);\n    }\n\n    private static void createNioCachedTable(Connection connection) throws SQLException {\n        try (Statement statement = connection.createStatement()) {\n            statement.execute(\"SET FILES LOG FALSE\");\n            statement.execute(\"SET FILES NIO TRUE\");\n            statement.execute(\"CREATE CACHED TABLE entries (id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY, payload VARBINARY(2048))\");\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static void insertRows(Connection connection, byte[] payload) throws SQLException {\n        boolean originalAutoCommit = connection.getAutoCommit();\n\n        connection.setAutoCommit(false);\n\n        try (PreparedStatement statement = connection.prepareStatement(\"INSERT INTO entries VALUES (?, ?)\")) {\n            for (int id = 1; id <= ROW_COUNT; id++) {\n                statement.setInt(1, id);\n                statement.setBytes(2, payload);\n                statement.addBatch();\n\n                if (id % BATCH_SIZE == 0) {\n                    statement.executeBatch();\n                    connection.commit();\n                }\n            }\n\n            statement.executeBatch();\n            connection.commit();\n        } finally {\n            connection.setAutoCommit(originalAutoCommit);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static void assertCachedDataIsReadable(Connection connection, byte[] payload) throws SQLException {\n        try (Statement statement = connection.createStatement()) {\n            try (ResultSet resultSet = statement.executeQuery(\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM entries\")) {\n                assertTrue(resultSet.next());\n                assertEquals(ROW_COUNT, resultSet.getInt(1));\n            }\n        }\n\n        try (PreparedStatement statement = connection.prepareStatement(\"SELECT payload FROM entries WHERE id = ?\")) {\n            statement.setInt(1, ROW_COUNT);\n\n            try (ResultSet resultSet = statement.executeQuery()) {\n                assertTrue(resultSet.next());\n                assertArrayEquals(payload, resultSet.getBytes(1));\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static void shutdown(Connection connection) throws SQLException {\n        try (Statement statement = connection.createStatement()) {\n            statement.execute(\"SHUTDOWN\");\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static byte[] createPayload() {\n        byte[] payload = new byte[PAYLOAD_SIZE];\n\n        for (int i = 0; i < payload.length; i++) {\n            payload[i] = (byte) (i % 251);\n        }\n\n        return payload;\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2330, "output": 2086, "cacheRead": 49152, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 53568, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777933471270, "responseId": "resp_0a23d5d0603067150169f91c9fdc9c81a1b37d9899e302cf98"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_apqT5nh0GPRGclBEOE9klq6Q|fc_0a23d5d0603067150169f91cb075a481a1ad133b81e6e4c8ab", "toolName": "write", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully wrote 4327 bytes to tests/src/org.hsqldb/hsqldb/2.4.1/src/test/java/org_hsqldb/hsqldb